<concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="topic_4_4">
   <title>Adding Reports to a Dashboard</title>
   <conbody>
    <p>After you have saved the dashboard, you will see the name of the dashboard that you provided
      in the upper left corner of the screen. The new dashboard will be empty with only one large
      "Add a Report" icon.</p>
    <p>Figure 3-5: Adding a Report to a Dashboard</p>
    <p><image href="./media/Image_125.jpg" height="151" width="457" id="image_qgd_43m_zx"/></p>
    <p>To add reports to the dashboard:</p>
    <ol id="ol_rgd_43m_zx">
      <li>Either click the large "Add a Report" or click the "Gear" icon for the dashboard settings
        menu and select "New Report Pod."<p>
          <note>Each report pod contains one report.<p>Figure 3-6: Naming the Dashboard
            Pod</p></note>
        </p><p><image href="./media/Image_126.jpg" height="222" width="612" id="image_sgd_43m_zx"
          /></p></li>
      <li>If desired, enter an optional name for the dashboard pod. Refer to Figure 3-6 for an
        example: </li>
      <li>To select the run configuration for the dashboard pod report, click the dropdown triangle
        to the right of the box below and select one of the followng:<ol id="ol_sbj_kkm_zx">
          <li><b>Most Recent AdHoc</b> retrieves report data from the user’s latest run of the
            specified report. </li>
          <li><b>Most Recent Scheduled</b> retrieves report data from the latest scheduled results
            of the specified report.</li>
          <li>
            <b>Always Re-Run</b> always re-runs report data to show current results and saves it to
              history.<p>Figure 3-7: Naming the Dashboard Pod</p><p><image
                href="./media/Image_128.jpg" height="272" width="610" id="image_ugd_43m_zx"
            /></p></li>
        </ol></li>
      <li> To select the report, click the dropdown triangle on the right of the box below the label
        "Select the report to display in this dashboard pod. To find the report you want to add,
        scroll through the dropdown list to find the report or type part of the report name in the
        search box.<p>Figure 3-8: Finding and Selecting a Report for a Dashboard</p><p>
          <image href="./media/Image_129.jpg" id="image_vgd_43m_zx" placement="break" scale="50"/>
        </p><p>
          <note>By default the pod will be named the same as the report you select. The pod
            name is displayed as the title in the green heading on each report pod. You can change
            this from the report name by editing the box “Dashboard pod name."</note>
        </p></li>
      <li>If the report you are adding has parameterized filters, you will see a grid with the list
        of filters. You can specify the Operator and Parameter value for each parameter. If the
        parameters are required, you must provide these values in order to save the report.<p>Figure
          3-9: List of Parameterized Filters for Dashboard Pod</p><p>
          <image href="./media/Image_130.jpg" id="image_wgd_43m_zx" placement="break" scale="55"/>
        </p></li>
      <li>If a chart has been configured for the report, the area of the screen below your parameter
        settings will have options to display either the chart, the grid, or both. To do this, click
        the checkboxes corresponding to the "Show Charts" and "Show Grid" labels.<p>Figure 3-10:
          Show Charts or Grids for Report on Dashboard Pod</p><p><image href="./media/Image_131.jpg"
            height="99" width="514" id="image_xgd_43m_zx"/></p></li>
      <li>If a field has been selected as the limit for the date and time range of the report, you
        have the option of changing the date and time range limit on the "Date and Time Range"
        tab.<note>NOTE: Click Now for current date and time, or click applicable dates in the
          calendar choosing the month and the year through the dropdown and choosing the date for
          the desired month and dragging the slider for desired hour, minute, and second. C</note></li>
      <li>Click Done.<p>The date and time are automatically populated in the Date and Time Range
          box. NEW SCREENSHOT NEEDED</p><p>Figure 3-11: Date and Time Range for Dashboard Pod</p><p>
          <image href="./media/Image_132.jpg" id="image_ygd_43m_zx" placement="break" scale="55"/>
        </p></li>
      <li>Click Save Pod.<p>You will see the dashboard now displayed with your specified report as
          shown in the sample below.</p><p>Figure 3-12: Dashboard with Report Display</p><p><image
            href="./media/Image_133.jpg" height="316" width="599" id="image_zgd_43m_zx"/></p><p>
          <note>If necessary, you can return to the previous screens to modify the settings of
            the pod. To do this, hover the mouse over the upper right corner of a pod until the pod
            settings icon is displayed; click this icon to view the pod settings menu and select
            Settings…</note>
        </p><p> Figure 3-13: Dashboard Pod Display</p><p><image href="./media/Image_134.jpg"
            height="347" width="616" id="image_ahd_43m_zx"/></p></li>
      <li>You can repeat steps 1-7 up to twenty times to add other reports to the dashboard.</li>
    </ol>
  </conbody>
</concept>
